Siberian weather conditions across
Ukraine left 30 people dead and forced the government to shut
schools across the country as temperatures plunged below 20
degrees Celsius, the Ministry for Emergency Situations said.  More than 544 people were hospitalized for frostbite, the
ministry said today in a  statement  on the government website.  The country closed 3,211 schools as of yesterday, according
to the  Education Ministry . Schools in the capital Kiev will
close from tomorrow until Feb. 5 as temperatures are forecast to
drop below 28 degrees Celsius, the cityâ€™s council press office
said today in an e-mailed statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
